Naive Bayes MCQ
You receive an email containing the words “free” and “win”.
How does Naive Bayes determine if it is spam?

ANSWER = Naive Bayes multiplies the probabilities of the words given each class and chooses the class with the highest probability.
Words like “free” and “win” appear more often in spam emails, so:

👉 Probability of Spam becomes higher..

